result.formatted_address: 51 Tsing King Rd, Tsing Yi, Hong Kong
result.name: Olbye Café

reviews.text:
Location: the restaurant is hidden between the public swimming pool. But, in fact, it is only a few minutes walk from the Tsing Yi MTR station. You have to pass through the opened gate then to see the low profiled restaurant.

Food: They have sets for lunch, afternoon tea and dinner.  The quality is in general good especially pork loin chop and side dishes.  The potato wedge is not recommended. In summer, they will serve iced lemon water which is a point to score consider its price.

Price: around 80 -100 for lunch and 100-150 for dinner per person. No service charge or tips is required. 

Staff: staff is friendly, if you are going with kids, the staff there will make conversation with your kids and provide them with plastic tablewares.
Nice cost price. Clean and wide space. So so food quality.

Nice environment and waitress.
Good place to have gathering with friends and family.
Small but nice local restaurant, reasonable priced manual and good service.

It is a cafe in the annex of Tsing Yi public swimming pool (no poolside view, sorry). Food and drinks are reasonably priced and in good portions but they are merely of average quality. The ambiance is nice and pleasantly quiet during off-peak.

result.adr_address: 青敬路51號, Tsing Yi, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 青敬路51號, Tsing Yi, Hong Kong
result.name: Tsing Yi Swimming Pool

reviews.text:
4 pools including a kids pool, Olympic size pool and two pools for learners. In addition three water slides.

Change rooms are spacious but run down with about half the lockers broken. 

Plenty of deck chairs if you arrive early enough.

Staff are relaxed allowing the kids to run around and play with water guns.

Overall a good way to relax.

This swimming pool have varieties of pools that serves children, elderlies and disabled, as well as hardcore swimmers. The only complain I have is that the practice pool is too crowded. Also, there are often swimming classes in session.
Unfortunately the slides were closed on my visit and one of the pools also, very busy in the other deepish leisure pool as lessons were taking place and no room to swim.
Clean. Well run with friendly staff.
Beautiful place.
